<item>
            <title>[SPARK-9956] Spark ML trees and ensembles fail for categorical features with 1 category</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-9956</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Spark ML trees and ensembles can be given metadata (e.g., from VectorIndexer) indicating that a certain feature is categorical with a single possible value.  This causes learning to fail.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Proposal: For now, fix this by making sure the algorithm still runs with such a feature, and remove the checks (which currently cause failure).  In the future, we can filter out these features to improve performance when there are many useless features.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
